<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_2891"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2891-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2891">Open publicly funded research results&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/0-4049">patrick.murphy.email</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">9 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Publicly funded research results are typically published in a journal that requires a subscription. Results should be published online, free for anyone to access. This could be accomplished quite simply by making open publishing a condition of the research grant. </div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2891" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2891', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2236&topicID=2891')">Comments (6)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2891"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2236">Making Data More Accessible</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=publishing research">publishing research</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2891"></div>
