<a href="/akira/dtd/2811-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2811">Stop the Presidential Debates being run by the Democratic Party and the GOP&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/0-4049">jmdean</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">9 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">The Presidential Debates are obviously very influential, but they are currently run by the Commission on Presidential Debates, which, in turn, is run by the Democratic Party and the Republican Party.  This is fundamentally undemocratic.<br/><br/>It may make better television to have a "head-to-head" debate, but the election of the President is too important for that and more voices need to be heard by the nation.</div>
