<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_2760"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2760-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2760">Limit government use of classified satellite data&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/0-4049">deep_harm</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">9 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">The Problem:  In 2007, the Bush administration decided to allow more federal agencies to use data from intelligence satellites, i.e., classified data. Nearly all federal agencies these days use satellite imagery, but non-classified imagery is adequate to meet most non-intel needs based on my experience as a GIS specialist at a federal homeland security agency.  To oversee the distribution of that data, the Bush administration proposed to establish a new government entity that included no external oversight of potential privacy violations resulting from the new policy.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2760" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2760', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2236&topicID=2760')">Comments (3)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2760"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2236">Making Data More Accessible</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=data">data</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=accessibility">accessibility</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=mapping">mapping</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=satellite">satellite</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=gis">gis</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=disasters">disasters</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2760"></div>
